Sentencas: An in-depth analysis of the very low frequency impedance arcs observed when measuring efficient solid oxide fuel cell electrodes by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) is reported in this paper.
Titulo: Identification and modelling of the oxygen gas diffusion impedance in SOFC porous electrodes: application to Pr2NiO4+δ

Sentencas: The study was carried out on Pr2NiO4+delta//Ce0.8Gd0.2O2- (delta)//3 mol.% Y2O3-ZrO2 symmetrical half-cell.
Titulo: Identification and modelling of the oxygen gas diffusion impedance in SOFC porous electrodes: application to Pr2NiO4+δ

Sentencas: In the temperature range 500-900 degrees C, three impedance arcs related to O-2 molecular diffusion were distinguished from the EIS measurements.
Titulo: Identification and modelling of the oxygen gas diffusion impedance in SOFC porous electrodes: application to Pr2NiO4+δ

Sentencas: Based on theoretical calculations using the Adler-Lane-Steele (ALS) and Dusty gas models, the arc at highest frequencies was ascribed to the diffusion of O-2 in the porous structures of the electrode and collecting gold grid.
Titulo: Identification and modelling of the oxygen gas diffusion impedance in SOFC porous electrodes: application to Pr2NiO4+δ

Sentencas: It obeys the ALS model, i.e. a parallel R//C impedance with a capacitance coming mainly from the solid phase.
Titulo: Identification and modelling of the oxygen gas diffusion impedance in SOFC porous electrodes: application to Pr2NiO4+δ

Sentencas: The second arc at medium frequencies was ascribed to the diffusion of O-2 in the porous structure of the ceramic part used to maintain the gold grid.
Titulo: Identification and modelling of the oxygen gas diffusion impedance in SOFC porous electrodes: application to Pr2NiO4+δ

Sentencas: It follows the Dusty gas model, i.e. a Warburg impedance with relaxation time depending on the gas phase properties.
Titulo: Identification and modelling of the oxygen gas diffusion impedance in SOFC porous electrodes: application to Pr2NiO4+δ

Sentencas: Finally, the third one at lowest frequencies was ascribed to the gas conversion phenomenon, coming from a difference in the local pO(2) above the active sites of the working and counter electrodes.
Titulo: Identification and modelling of the oxygen gas diffusion impedance in SOFC porous electrodes: application to Pr2NiO4+δ

Sentencas: This gas conversion impedance largely increases when clogging the channels of the gas distribution system.
Titulo: Identification and modelling of the oxygen gas diffusion impedance in SOFC porous electrodes: application to Pr2NiO4+δ
